The core gateway confirms two things already: `swapAndMultiBridge` has a real infinite loop in the ratio aggregation, and `executeRoute`/`executeRoutes` are generic delegatecall dispatchers by design, so those are not findings on their own. I’m now checking whether the bridge entrypoints actually spend pre-existing gateway balances or whether they pull from the current caller first.
